 Japanese Characters&quot; has the swastika listed as both a clockwise and counterclockwise symbol.  It's listed under possible origins for &quot;man&quot; (means ten-thousand, looks like katakana &quot;ka&quot; with a line on top). Here is what it says in the book:<br>
